{"type":"message","id":"df83840d","parentId":"8342df94","timestamp":"2026-03-04T01:06:20.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"我看到Alpha Vantage有新闻情绪数据。让我尝试用Alpha Vantage来获取新闻，并看返回的数据是否包含热度分数。\n\n让我先用EODHD来获取财经新闻，这个成功率高。","thinkingSignature":"771fe99da55557160dff7d15ff0bb59b6051c2479c32c939a1e66504fe08120b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1l8vv9d95kba_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs execute eodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c --params '{\"limit\": 30}'","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":19635,"output":118,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772586373766}}
{"type":"message","id":"3fa2b5d3","parentId":"df83840d","timestamp":"2026-03-04T01:06:25.277Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1l8vv9d95kba_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"1b4da419-1bbe-448a-ac47-96a49489edce\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (634947 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2Fd6076705c09e4d66b3899fa73fe3355c.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772593584&Signature=8mDH9hqrEHw27v4EGFzneU65mIo%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:32:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Why Intel (INTC) Stock Is Falling Today\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What Happened?\\\\n\\\\nShares of computer processor maker Intel (NASDAQ:INTC) fell 4.5% in the afternoon session after escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East sparked a surge in oil prices and stoked fears of a wider economic conflict, as Trump warned the conflict could last up to a month.\\\\n\\\\nThe sell-off was broad, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average falling by more than 1,000 points, while the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite each dropped over 2%. Investor anxiety centered on a conflict involving Iran, which reportedly led to the shutdown of the Strait of Hormuz, a critical channel for global oil shipping. The disruption sent oil prices soaring, with international benchmark Brent crude topping $84 a barrel. These higher energy costs are fueling concerns about worsening inflation, which could further pressure households and businesses, and investors are growing worried that a prolonged conflict could inflict sustained damage on the global economy.\\\\n\\\\nThe shares closed the day at $43.08, down 5.3% from previous close.\\\\n\\\\nThe stock market overreacts to news, and big price drops can present good opportunities to buy high-quality stocks. Is now the time to buy Intel? Access our full analysis report here, it’s free.\\\\n\\\\nWhat Is The Market Telling Us\\\\n\\\\nIntel’s shares are extremely volatile and have had 41 moves greater than 5% over the last year. In that context, today’s move indicates the market considers this news meaningful but not something that would fundamentally change its perception of the business.\\\\n\\\\nThe previous big move we wrote about was 7 days ago when the stock gained 5.4% on the news that the semiconductor sector received a major boost as Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) secured a deal to sell up to US$60 billion in artificial intelligence chips to Meta Platforms over five years.\\\\n\\\\nThis landmark agreement, which also allows Meta to purchase as much as 10% of the chip firm, is one of the latest blockbuster deals in the artificial intelligence space, signaling massive investment by tech giants. The news prompted a significant rally in AMD's shares, which jumped more than 10% in premarket trading. The deal not only highlights the immense demand for specialized AI hardware but also contributed to a broader rebound in technology stocks, helping to ease recent investor fears about the disruptive impacts of AI.\\\\n\\\\nIntel is up 9.2% since the beginning of the year, but at $42.99 per share, it is still trading 20.9% below its 52-week high of $54.32 from January 2026. Investors who bought $1,000 worth of Intel’s shares 5 years ago would now be looking at an investment worth $717.61.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nWHILE YOU’RE HERE: The Next Palantir? One satellite company captures images of every point on Earth. Every single day. The Pentagon wants it. Hedge funds are using it to beat earnings. You’ve probably never heard of it.\\\\n\\\\nThis is what the early days of Palantir looked like before it became a $437 billion giant. Same playbook. Different technology. If you missed Palantir, you need to see this. Claim The Stock Ticker for Free HERE.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/why-intel-intc-stock-falling-003242694.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"1INTC.MI\\\", \\\"AMD.US\\\", \\\"CL.COMM\\\", \\\"DJI.INDX\\\", \\\"GSPC.INDX\\\", \\\"INTC.BA\\\", \\\"INTC.MX\\\", \\\"INTC.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"GEOPOLITICAL-TENSIONS\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"OIL-PRICES\\\", \\\"SEMICONDUCTORS\\\", \\\"TECH\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.992, \\\"neg\\\": 0.073, \\\"neu\\\": 0.789, \\\"pos\\\": 0.138}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:27:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Why AMD (AMD) Stock Is Trading Lower Today\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What Happened?\\\\n\\\\nShares of computer processor maker AMD (NASDAQ:AMD) fell 3.6% in the afternoon session after escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East sparked a surge in oil prices and stoked fears of a wider economic conflict, as Trump warned the conflict could last up to a month.\\\\n\\\\nThe sell-off was broad, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average falling by more than 1,000 points, while the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite each dropped over 2%. Investor anxiety centered on a conflict involving Iran, which reportedly led to the shutdown of the Strait of Hormuz, a critical channel for global oil shipping. The disruption sent oil prices soaring, with international benchmark Brent crude topping $84 a barrel. These higher energy costs are fueling concerns about worsening inflation, which could further pressure households and businesses, and investors are growing worried that a prolonged conflict could inflict sustained damage on the global economy.\\\\n\\\\nThe shares closed the day at $190.95, down 3.9% from previous close.\\\\n\\\\nThe stock market overreacts to news, and big price drops can present good opportunities to buy high-quality stocks. Is now the time to buy AMD? Access our full analysis report here, it’s free.\\\\n\\\\nWhat Is The Market Telling Us\\\\n\\\\nAMD’s shares are extremely volatile and have had 34 moves greater than 5% over the last year. In that context, today’s move indicates the market considers this news meaningful but not something that would fundamentally change its perception of the business.\\\\n\\\\nThe previous big move we wrote about was 7 days ago when the stock gained 8.5% on the news that the company secured a deal to sell up to US$60 billion in artificial intelligence chips to Meta Platforms over five years.\\\\n\\\\nThis landmark agreement, which also allows Meta to purchase as much as 10% of the chip firm, is one of the latest blockbuster deals in the artificial intelligence space, signaling massive investment by tech giants. The deal not only highlights the immense demand for specialized AI hardware but also contributed to a broader rebound in technology stocks, helping to ease recent investor fears about the disruptive impacts of AI.\\\\n\\\\nAMD is down 14.7% since the beginning of the year, and at $190.69 per share, it is trading 27.9% below its 52-week high of $264.33 from October 2025. Investors who bought $1,000 worth of AMD’s shares 5 years ago would now be looking at an investment worth $2,358.\\\\n\\\\nALSO WORTH WATCHING: Nvidia’s Quiet Partner. Nvidia’s chips cost a hundred grand. The connectors that make them work cost even more. One company makes them all.\\\\n\\\\nEvery AI server needs specialized infrastructure the chip companies don’t make. High-speed cables. Power connectors. Thermal sensors. This 90-year-old company built a monopoly on it. The AI boom just started. This stock is still flying under the radar. Claim The Stock Ticker Here for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/why-amd-amd-stock-trading-002742987.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"AMD.US\\\", \\\"CL.COMM\\\", \\\"DJI.INDX\\\", \\\"GSPC.INDX\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ARTIFICIAL-INTELLIGENCE\\\", \\\"GEOPOLITICAL-TENSIONS\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"OIL-PRICES\\\", \\\"TECHNOLOGY\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.991, \\\"neg\\\": 0.073, \\\"neu\\\": 0.791, \\\"pos\\\": 0.136}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:23:25+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Novo Nordisk Deepens Oral GLP 1 Bet With Vivtex Deal And Ireland Spend\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Never miss an important update on your stock portfolio and cut through the noise. Over 7 million investors trust Simply Wall St to stay informed where it matters for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nNovo Nordisk has entered a partnership with Vivtex to develop next generation oral biologic medicines for obesity and diabetes. The company has approved a €432 million investment to expand its oral tablet manufacturing facility in Ireland. The expansion is aimed at increasing capacity for oral GLP-1 treatments, including the newly FDA approved oral Wegovy.\\\\n\\\\nNovo Nordisk, traded as CPSE:NOVO B, is leaning further into oral treatments at a time when its share price stands at DKK231.5. The stock has seen sizeable volatility, with a 37.4% decline over the past 30 days and a 61.4% decline over the past year, while still showing a 14.1% gain over five years. These moves provide important context for investors assessing how new projects in oral obesity and diabetes care fit into the broader story.\\\\n\\\\nThe Vivtex partnership and Irish capacity build out focus on oral GLP-1 medicines that have historically relied on injections. For you as an investor, the key questions are how effectively Novo Nordisk can turn these initiatives into viable products at scale and how that might influence its role in obesity and diabetes treatment over time.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Novo Nordisk by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Novo Nordisk.CPSE:NOVO B Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\n📰 Beyond the headline: 5 risks and 4 things going right for Novo Nordisk that every investor should see.\\\\n\\\\nThe Vivtex partnership and the €432 million Athlone investment point in the same direction: Novo Nordisk is trying to secure a meaningful position in oral GLP-1 treatments rather than rely only on injectables. Vivtex brings drug delivery technology designed to improve how large biologic molecules are absorbed in the gut, while Novo puts its weight behind large scale production capacity in Ireland for oral Wegovy and future GLP-1 tablets. For you, the link between the two is important. If oral formulations continue to gain traction in obesity and diabetes care, the combination of proprietary delivery know how and dedicated tabletting capacity could matter for how competitive Novo Nordisk is versus Eli Lilly and other large pharma peers that are also working on oral GLP-1s.\\\\n\\\\nHow This Fits Into The Novo Nordisk Narrative\\\\n\\\\nThe Athlone expansion supports the existing narrative that future returns may rely increasingly on oral obesity treatments by adding capacity for current and pipeline GLP-1 tablets. The scale of investment and partnership related spending could pressure free cash flow in the near term, which connects to concerns in the narrative about high capital expenditure and earnings quality if demand is less robust than expected. The Vivtex collaboration introduces a new oral biologics platform that is not fully reflected in the earlier narrative focus on Wegovy, Ozempic and existing injectable and oral pipelines.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nKnowing what a company is worth starts with understanding its story. Check out one of the top narratives in the Simply Wall St Community for Novo Nordisk to help decide what it is worth to you.\\\\n\\\\nThe Risks and Rewards Investors Should Consider\\\\n\\\\n⚠️ Large manufacturing projects and external technology partnerships add execution risk, especially if regulatory timelines or physician uptake for oral GLP-1s differ from expectations. ⚠️ Analysts have flagged five key risks for Novo Nordisk, including share price volatility and concerns around earnings quality, which can influence how the market reacts to heavy investment in new formats like oral biologics. 🎁 The Ireland expansion is expected to increase supply for oral GLP-1 products outside the US, which could help address past capacity constraints if demand for oral Wegovy and similar drugs remains strong. 🎁 The Vivtex agreement gives Novo Nordisk access to a gastrointestinal screening and AI supported formulation platform that is specifically designed for oral biologic medicines, potentially broadening its future product range beyond current GLP-1 offerings.\\\\n\\\\nWhat To Watch Going Forward\\\\n\\\\nFrom here, you may want to watch three things. First, how quickly physicians and patients adopt oral Wegovy versus injectable options as more data and real world experience build up. Second, concrete milestones from the Vivtex collaboration, such as selection of lead oral biologic candidates or movement into clinical trials. Third, progress at the Athlone site, including whether the project stays on time and on budget as construction runs through 2028. These will help you judge whether Novo Nordisk is turning its spend on oral technologies and capacity into a sustainable position in obesity and diabetes care.\\\\n\\\\nTo ensure you are always in the loop on how the latest news impacts the investment narrative for Novo Nordisk, head to the community page for Novo Nordisk to never miss an update on the top community narratives.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include NOVO-B.CO.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/novo-nordisk-deepens-oral-glp-002325017.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"NONOF.US\\\", \\\"NOVO-B.US\\\", \\\"NVO.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"DIABETES\\\", \\\"FREE CASH FLOW\\\", \\\"INVESTMENTS\\\", \\\"OBESITY\\\", \\\"ORAL-BIOLOGICS\\\", \\\"PHARMA\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.02, \\\"neu\\\": 0.856, \\\"pos\\\": 0.124}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:22:54+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Cisco Deepens AI And 6G Push With Secure Australia Factory\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Make better investment decisions with Simply Wall St's easy, visual tools that give you a competitive edge.\\\\n\\\\nCisco Systems (NasdaqGS:CSCO) has joined major global collaborations focused on open, AI native 6G wireless networks. The company is working with telecom and technology partners to shape standards and architectures for next generation connectivity. Cisco has launched Australia’s first Cisco Secure AI Factory with SharonAI Holdings and NVIDIA, focused on sovereign AI infrastructure and data security.\\\\n\\\\nCisco Systems sits at the center of networking and security for large enterprises and telecom operators, so its push into AI centric 6G and secure AI infrastructure fits within its core business. For investors tracking longer term themes such as AI workloads, edge computing and secure data handling, these moves help explain how Cisco aims to stay relevant as traffic patterns and compute needs evolve.\\\\n\\\\nThe new partnerships and the Secure AI Factory in Australia provide a view of where Cisco is placing its time and capital. As these projects progress, points to monitor include customer adoption, ecosystem support and how effectively Cisco can convert these technology efforts into revenue streams across its hardware, software and services lines.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Cisco Systems by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Cisco Systems.NasdaqGS:CSCO Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\n4 things going right for Cisco Systems that this headline doesn't cover.\\\\n\\\\nCisco’s involvement in AI native 6G collaborations and the Cisco Secure AI Factory in Australia pulls the company further into two areas investors are watching closely: next generation telecom standards and AI data center infrastructure. Working alongside NVIDIA, Ericsson, Nokia and major carriers gives Cisco a seat at the table as 6G architectures and interoperability get defined, which can be important for future product roadmaps in routing, switching and security. The Australian AI Factory, built on Cisco’s UCS servers, security stack and networking portfolio with NVIDIA GPUs and VAST Data storage, shows how Cisco packages its hardware and software into full-stack AI offerings rather than just selling point products. For you as an investor, the key question is whether these collaborations translate into repeatable, high value deployments across sectors like utilities, telecom and government, rather than remaining one off showcase projects. Cisco’s presence at events like Mobile World Congress and optical networking conferences also reinforces its push in AI optimized Ethernet and data center connectivity, areas where it competes with Arista Networks and Juniper Networks.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nHow This Fits Into The Cisco Systems Narrative\\\\n\\\\nThe 6G and AI networking collaborations align with the narrative that Cisco is targeting growing AI infrastructure demand and integrating security into its networking portfolio. A heavy focus on complex joint offerings with partners like NVIDIA could increase execution risk around delivering recurring software and services revenue at the pace the narrative outlines. The sovereign AI angle of the Secure AI Factory and the specific Australian deployment are not fully reflected in the broader narrative about global AI infrastructure demand and may add another dimension to Cisco’s story in government and regulated industries.\\\\n\\\\nKnowing what a company is worth starts with understanding its story. Check out one of the top narratives in the Simply Wall St Community for Cisco Systems to help decide what it is worth to you.\\\\n\\\\nThe Risks and Rewards Investors Should Consider\\\\n\\\\n⚠️ Cisco’s growing dependence on large AI infrastructure projects with a small number of cloud and telecom partners could expose investors to swings in project timing or spending decisions. ⚠️ Analysts have highlighted execution risk in shifting to recurring revenue and scaling new software and security lines, and complex AI collaborations may add to that operational challenge. 🎁 Participation in AI native 6G and high performance AI networking places Cisco alongside leading players such as NVIDIA in markets where demand for data center and edge connectivity is expanding. 🎁 The Cisco Secure AI Factory model, focused on sovereign AI and data residency, could appeal to governments and regulated sectors that need in country AI infrastructure and strong security.\\\\n\\\\nWhat To Watch Going Forward\\\\n\\\\nFrom here, keep an eye on whether Cisco announces additional Secure AI Factory style deployments in other countries, and how often it references these AI and 6G collaborations in future conference presentations and client announcements. Watch for concrete metrics such as the number of AI customers using Cisco’s full stack platforms, or comments on AI related order pipelines in earnings calls, to gauge whether these partnerships are turning into material hardware, software and services revenue. Competitive responses from peers like Arista Networks, Juniper Networks and Nokia in AI networking and 6G standard setting will also help you judge Cisco’s position. Finally, track any analyst commentary that links these projects to Cisco’s long term earnings visibility or to key risks around dependence on hyperscale and telecom spending.\\\\n\\\\nTo ensure you are always in the loop on how the latest news impacts the investment narrative for Cisco Systems, head to the community page for Cisco Systems to avoid missing updates on the top community narratives.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include CSCO.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/cisco-deepens-ai-6g-push-002254216.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"CSCO.US\\\", \\\"NVDA.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"6G\\\", \\\"AI\\\", \\\"DATA-CENTERS\\\", \\\"NETWORKING\\\", \\\"TELECOM\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.021, \\\"neu\\\": 0.857, \\\"pos\\\": 0.122}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:22:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Semtech, Photronics, Nova, and Vishay Intertechnology Shares Are Falling, What You Need To Know\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What Happened?\\\\n\\\\nA number of stocks fell in the afternoon session after escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East sparked a surge in oil prices and stoked f\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"symbols\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"tags\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"sentiment\": {\n            \"anyOf\": [\n              {\n                \"type\": \"null\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                  \"polarity\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neg\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neu\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"pos\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  }\n                },\n                \"required\": [\n                  \"neg\",\n                  \"neu\",\n                  \"polarity\",\n                  \"pos\"\n                ]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"sentiment\",\n          \"symbols\",\n          \"tags\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 3279.31,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4735,"aggregated":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"1b4da419-1bbe-448a-ac47-96a49489edce\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (634947 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2Fd6076705c09e4d66b3899fa73fe3355c.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772593584&Signature=8mDH9hqrEHw27v4EGFzneU65mIo%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:32:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Why Intel (INTC) Stock Is Falling Today\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What Happened?\\\\n\\\\nShares of computer processor maker Intel (NASDAQ:INTC) fell 4.5% in the afternoon session after escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East sparked a surge in oil prices and stoked fears of a wider economic conflict, as Trump warned the conflict could last up to a month.\\\\n\\\\nThe sell-off was broad, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average falling by more than 1,000 points, while the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite each dropped over 2%. Investor anxiety centered on a conflict involving Iran, which reportedly led to the shutdown of the Strait of Hormuz, a critical channel for global oil shipping. The disruption sent oil prices soaring, with international benchmark Brent crude topping $84 a barrel. These higher energy costs are fueling concerns about worsening inflation, which could further pressure households and businesses, and investors are growing worried that a prolonged conflict could inflict sustained damage on the global economy.\\\\n\\\\nThe shares closed the day at $43.08, down 5.3% from previous close.\\\\n\\\\nThe stock market overreacts to news, and big price drops can present good opportunities to buy high-quality stocks. Is now the time to buy Intel? Access our full analysis report here, it’s free.\\\\n\\\\nWhat Is The Market Telling Us\\\\n\\\\nIntel’s shares are extremely volatile and have had 41 moves greater than 5% over the last year. In that context, today’s move indicates the market considers this news meaningful but not something that would fundamentally change its perception of the business.\\\\n\\\\nThe previous big move we wrote about was 7 days ago when the stock gained 5.4% on the news that the semiconductor sector received a major boost as Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) secured a deal to sell up to US$60 billion in artificial intelligence chips to Meta Platforms over five years.\\\\n\\\\nThis landmark agreement, which also allows Meta to purchase as much as 10% of the chip firm, is one of the latest blockbuster deals in the artificial intelligence space, signaling massive investment by tech giants. The news prompted a significant rally in AMD's shares, which jumped more than 10% in premarket trading. The deal not only highlights the immense demand for specialized AI hardware but also contributed to a broader rebound in technology stocks, helping to ease recent investor fears about the disruptive impacts of AI.\\\\n\\\\nIntel is up 9.2% since the beginning of the year, but at $42.99 per share, it is still trading 20.9% below its 52-week high of $54.32 from January 2026. Investors who bought $1,000 worth of Intel’s shares 5 years ago would now be looking at an investment worth $717.61.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nWHILE YOU’RE HERE: The Next Palantir? One satellite company captures images of every point on Earth. Every single day. The Pentagon wants it. Hedge funds are using it to beat earnings. You’ve probably never heard of it.\\\\n\\\\nThis is what the early days of Palantir looked like before it became a $437 billion giant. Same playbook. Different technology. If you missed Palantir, you need to see this. Claim The Stock Ticker for Free HERE.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/why-intel-intc-stock-falling-003242694.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"1INTC.MI\\\", \\\"AMD.US\\\", \\\"CL.COMM\\\", \\\"DJI.INDX\\\", \\\"GSPC.INDX\\\", \\\"INTC.BA\\\", \\\"INTC.MX\\\", \\\"INTC.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"GEOPOLITICAL-TENSIONS\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"OIL-PRICES\\\", \\\"SEMICONDUCTORS\\\", \\\"TECH\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.992, \\\"neg\\\": 0.073, \\\"neu\\\": 0.789, \\\"pos\\\": 0.138}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:27:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Why AMD (AMD) Stock Is Trading Lower Today\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"What Happened?\\\\n\\\\nShares of computer processor maker AMD (NASDAQ:AMD) fell 3.6% in the afternoon session after escalating geopolitical tensions in the Middle East sparked a surge in oil prices and stoked fears of a wider economic conflict, as Trump warned the conflict could last up to a month.\\\\n\\\\nThe sell-off was broad, with the Dow Jones Industrial Average falling by more than 1,000 points, while the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite each dropped over 2%. Investor anxiety centered on a conflict involving Iran, which reportedly led to the shutdown of the Strait of Hormuz, a critical channel for global oil shipping. The disruption sent oil prices soaring, with international benchmark Brent crude topping $84 a barrel. These higher energy costs are fueling concerns about worsening inflation, which could further pressure households and businesses, and investors are growing worried that a prolonged conflict could inflict sustained damage on the global economy.\\\\n\\\\nThe shares closed the day at $190.95, down 3.9% from previous close.\\\\n\\\\nThe stock market overreacts to news, and big price drops can present good opportunities to buy high-quality stocks. Is now the time to buy AMD? Access our full analysis report here, it’s free.\\\\n\\\\nWhat Is The Market Telling Us\\\\n\\\\nAMD’s shares are extremely volatile and have had 34 moves greater than 5% over the last year. In that context, today’s move indicates the market considers this news meaningful but not something that would fundamentally change its perception of the business.\\\\n\\\\nThe previous big move we wrote about was 7 days ago when the stock gained 8.5% on the news that the company secured a deal to sell up to US$60 billion in artificial intelligence chips to Meta Platforms over five years.\\\\n\\\\nThis landmark agreement, which also allows Meta to purchase as much as 10% of the chip firm, is one of the latest blockbuster deals in the artificial intelligence space, signaling massive investment by tech giants. The deal not only highlights the immense demand for specialized AI hardware but also contributed to a broader rebound in technology stocks, helping to ease recent investor fears about the disruptive impacts of AI.\\\\n\\\\nAMD is down 14.7% since the beginning of the year, and at $190.69 per share, it is trading 27.9% below its 52-week high of $264.33 from October 2025. Investors who bought $1,000 worth of AMD’s shares 5 years ago would now be looking at an investment worth $2,358.\\\\n\\\\nALSO WORTH WATCHING: Nvidia’s Quiet Partner. Nvidia’s chips cost a hundred grand. The connectors that make them work cost even more. One company makes them all.\\\\n\\\\nEvery AI server needs specialized infrastructure the chip companies don’t make. High-speed cables. Power connectors. Thermal sensors. This 90-year-old company built a monopoly on it. The AI boom just started. This stock is still flying under the radar. Claim The Stock Ticker Here for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/why-amd-amd-stock-trading-002742987.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"AMD.US\\\", \\\"CL.COMM\\\", \\\"DJI.INDX\\\", \\\"GSPC.INDX\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"ARTIFICIAL-INTELLIGENCE\\\", \\\"GEOPOLITICAL-TENSIONS\\\", \\\"INFLATION\\\", \\\"OIL-PRICES\\\", \\\"TECHNOLOGY\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.991, \\\"neg\\\": 0.073, \\\"neu\\\": 0.791, \\\"pos\\\": 0.136}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:23:25+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Novo Nordisk Deepens Oral GLP 1 Bet With Vivtex Deal And Ireland Spend\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Never miss an important update on your stock portfolio and cut through the noise. Over 7 million investors trust Simply Wall St to stay informed where it matters for FREE.\\\\n\\\\nNovo Nordisk has entered a partnership with Vivtex to develop next generation oral biologic medicines for obesity and diabetes. The company has approved a €432 million investment to expand its oral tablet manufacturing facility in Ireland. The expansion is aimed at increasing capacity for oral GLP-1 treatments, including the newly FDA approved oral Wegovy.\\\\n\\\\nNovo Nordisk, traded as CPSE:NOVO B, is leaning further into oral treatments at a time when its share price stands at DKK231.5. The stock has seen sizeable volatility, with a 37.4% decline over the past 30 days and a 61.4% decline over the past year, while still showing a 14.1% gain over five years. These moves provide important context for investors assessing how new projects in oral obesity and diabetes care fit into the broader story.\\\\n\\\\nThe Vivtex partnership and Irish capacity build out focus on oral GLP-1 medicines that have historically relied on injections. For you as an investor, the key questions are how effectively Novo Nordisk can turn these initiatives into viable products at scale and how that might influence its role in obesity and diabetes treatment over time.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Novo Nordisk by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Novo Nordisk.CPSE:NOVO B Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\n📰 Beyond the headline: 5 risks and 4 things going right for Novo Nordisk that every investor should see.\\\\n\\\\nThe Vivtex partnership and the €432 million Athlone investment point in the same direction: Novo Nordisk is trying to secure a meaningful position in oral GLP-1 treatments rather than rely only on injectables. Vivtex brings drug delivery technology designed to improve how large biologic molecules are absorbed in the gut, while Novo puts its weight behind large scale production capacity in Ireland for oral Wegovy and future GLP-1 tablets. For you, the link between the two is important. If oral formulations continue to gain traction in obesity and diabetes care, the combination of proprietary delivery know how and dedicated tabletting capacity could matter for how competitive Novo Nordisk is versus Eli Lilly and other large pharma peers that are also working on oral GLP-1s.\\\\n\\\\nHow This Fits Into The Novo Nordisk Narrative\\\\n\\\\nThe Athlone expansion supports the existing narrative that future returns may rely increasingly on oral obesity treatments by adding capacity for current and pipeline GLP-1 tablets. The scale of investment and partnership related spending could pressure free cash flow in the near term, which connects to concerns in the narrative about high capital expenditure and earnings quality if demand is less robust than expected. The Vivtex collaboration introduces a new oral biologics platform that is not fully reflected in the earlier narrative focus on Wegovy, Ozempic and existing injectable and oral pipelines.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nKnowing what a company is worth starts with understanding its story. Check out one of the top narratives in the Simply Wall St Community for Novo Nordisk to help decide what it is worth to you.\\\\n\\\\nThe Risks and Rewards Investors Should Consider\\\\n\\\\n⚠️ Large manufacturing projects and external technology partnerships add execution risk, especially if regulatory timelines or physician uptake for oral GLP-1s differ from expectations. ⚠️ Analysts have flagged five key risks for Novo Nordisk, including share price volatility and concerns around earnings quality, which can influence how the market reacts to heavy investment in new formats like oral biologics. 🎁 The Ireland expansion is expected to increase supply for oral GLP-1 products outside the US, which could help address past capacity constraints if demand for oral Wegovy and similar drugs remains strong. 🎁 The Vivtex agreement gives Novo Nordisk access to a gastrointestinal screening and AI supported formulation platform that is specifically designed for oral biologic medicines, potentially broadening its future product range beyond current GLP-1 offerings.\\\\n\\\\nWhat To Watch Going Forward\\\\n\\\\nFrom here, you may want to watch three things. First, how quickly physicians and patients adopt oral Wegovy versus injectable options as more data and real world experience build up. Second, concrete milestones from the Vivtex collaboration, such as selection of lead oral biologic candidates or movement into clinical trials. Third, progress at the Athlone site, including whether the project stays on time and on budget as construction runs through 2028. These will help you judge whether Novo Nordisk is turning its spend on oral technologies and capacity into a sustainable position in obesity and diabetes care.\\\\n\\\\nTo ensure you are always in the loop on how the latest news impacts the investment narrative for Novo Nordisk, head to the community page for Novo Nordisk to never miss an update on the top community narratives.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include NOVO-B.CO.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/novo-nordisk-deepens-oral-glp-002325017.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"NONOF.US\\\", \\\"NOVO-B.US\\\", \\\"NVO.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"DIABETES\\\", \\\"FREE CASH FLOW\\\", \\\"INVESTMENTS\\\", \\\"OBESITY\\\", \\\"ORAL-BIOLOGICS\\\", \\\"PHARMA\\\", \\\"SHARE PRICE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.02, \\\"neu\\\": 0.856, \\\"pos\\\": 0.124}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T00:22:54+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Cisco Deepens AI And 6G Push With Secure Australia Factory\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Make better investment decisions with Simply Wall St's easy, visual tools that give you a competitive edge.\\\\n\\\\nCisco Systems (NasdaqGS:CSCO) has joined major global collaborations focused on open, AI native 6G wireless networks. The company is working with telecom and technology partners to shape standards and architectures for next generation connectivity. Cisco has launched Australia’s first Cisco Secure AI Factory with SharonAI Holdings and NVIDIA, focused on sovereign AI infrastructure and data security.\\\\n\\\\nCisco Systems sits at the center of networking and security for large enterprises and telecom operators, so its push into AI centric 6G and secure AI infrastructure fits within its core business. For investors tracking longer term themes such as AI workloads, edge computing and secure data handling, these moves help explain how Cisco aims to stay relevant as traffic patterns and compute needs evolve.\\\\n\\\\nThe new partnerships and the Secure AI Factory in Australia provide a view of where Cisco is placing its time and capital. As these projects progress, points to monitor include customer adoption, ecosystem support and how effectively Cisco can convert these technology efforts into revenue streams across its hardware, software and services lines.\\\\n\\\\nStay updated on the most important news stories for Cisco Systems by adding it to your watchlist or portfolio. Alternatively, explore our Community to discover new perspectives on Cisco Systems.NasdaqGS:CSCO Earnings & Revenue Growth as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\n4 things going right for Cisco Systems that this headline doesn't cover.\\\\n\\\\nCisco’s involvement in AI native 6G collaborations and the Cisco Secure AI Factory in Australia pulls the company further into two areas investors are watching closely: next generation telecom standards and AI data center infrastructure. Working alongside NVIDIA, Ericsson, Nokia and major carriers gives Cisco a seat at the table as 6G architectures and interoperability get defined, which can be important for future product roadmaps in routing, switching and security. The Australian AI Factory, built on Cisco’s UCS servers, security stack and networking portfolio with NVIDIA GPUs and VAST Data storage, shows how Cisco packages its hardware and software into full-stack AI offerings rather than just selling point products. For you as an investor, the key question is whether these collaborations translate into repeatable, high value deployments across sectors like utilities, telecom and government, rather than remaining one off showcase projects. Cisco’s presence at events like Mobile World Congress and optical networking conferences also reinforces its push in AI optimized Ethernet and data center connectivity, areas where it competes with Arista Networks and Juniper Networks.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nHow This Fits Into The Cisco Systems Narrative\\\\n\\\\nThe 6G and AI networking collaborations align with the narrative that Cisco is targeting growing AI infrastructure demand and integrating security into its networking portfolio. A heavy focus on complex joint offerings with partners like NVIDIA could increase execution risk around delivering recurring software and services revenue at the pace the narrative outlines. The sovereign AI angle of the Secure AI Factory and the specific Australian deployment are not fully reflected in the broader narrative about global AI infrastructure demand and may add another dimension to Cisco’s story in government and regulated industries.\\\\n\\\\nKnowing what a company is worth starts with understanding its story. Check out one of the top narratives in the Simply Wall St Community for Cisco Systems to help decide what it is worth to you.\\\\n\\\\nThe Risks and Rewards Investors Should Consider\\\\n\\\\n⚠️ Cisco’s growing dependence on large AI infrastructure projects with a small number of cloud and telecom partners could expose investors to swings in project timing or spending decisions. ⚠️ Analysts have highlighted execution risk in shifting to recurring revenue and scaling new software and security lines, and complex AI collaborations may add to that operational challenge. 🎁 Participation in AI native 6G and high performance AI networking places Cisco alongside leading players such as NVIDIA in markets where demand for data center and edge connectivity is expanding. 🎁 The Cisco Secure AI Factory model, focused on sovereign AI and data residency, could appeal to governments and regulated sectors that need in country AI infrastructure and strong security.\\\\n\\\\nWhat To Watch Going Forward\\\\n\\\\nFrom here, keep an eye on whether Cisco announces additional Secure AI Factory style deployments in other countries, and how often it references these AI and 6G collaborations in future conference presentations and client announcements. Watch for concrete metrics such as the number of AI customers using Cisco’s full stack platforms, or comments on AI related order pipelines in earnings calls, to gauge whether these partnerships are turning into material hardware, software and services revenue. Competitive responses from peers like Arista Networks, Juniper Networks and Nokia in AI networking and 6G standard setting will also help you judge Cisco’s position. Finally, track any analyst commentary that links these projects to Cisco’s long term earnings visibility or to key risks around dependence on hyperscale and telecom spending.\\\\n\\\\nTo ensure you are always in the loop on how the latest news impacts the investment narrative for Cisco Systems, head to the community page for Cisco Systems to avoid missing updates on the top community narratives.\\\\n\\\\nThis article by Simply Wall St is general in nature. We provide commentary based on historical data and analyst forecasts only using an unbiased methodology and our articles are not intended to be financial advice. It does not constitute a recommendation to buy or sell any stock, and does not take account of your objectives, or your financial situation. We aim to bring you long-term focused analysis driven by fundamental data. Note that our analysis may not factor in the latest price-sensitive company announcements or qualitative material. Simply Wall St has no position in any stocks mentioned.\\\\n\\\\nCompanies discussed in this article include CSCO.\\\\n\\\\nHave feedback on this article? Concerned about the content? Get in touch with us directly. Alternatively, email editorial-team@simplywallst.com\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/cisco-deepens-ai-6g-push-002254216.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"CSCO.US\\\", \\\"NVDA.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"6G\\\", \\\"AI\\\", \\\"DATA-CENTERS\\\", \\\"NETWORKING\\\", \\\"TELECOM\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998